com.innowhere.jnieasy.core.method
Interface NativeInstanceFieldMethod

All Superinterfaces:
NativeBehavior, NativeCapable, NativeFieldMethod
All Known Subinterfaces:
NativeDirectInstanceFieldCallback, NativeInstanceFieldCallback, NativeInstanceFieldMethodReflection
public interface NativeInstanceFieldMethod
extends NativeFieldMethod

The NativeInstanceFieldMethod is the interface implemented by native capable classes that bridges Java and native instance fields seen as methods.

Author:
Jose M. Arranz Santamaria

call

java.lang.Object call(java.lang.Object obj,
                      int opcode,
                      java.lang.Object value)
Calls the native field-method to get/set the value of the related native field.

The specified value must match the native type of the field. Returned value type will match the native type of the field.

If opcode is:

  • NativeFieldMethod.GET : returns the current field value. The value is ignored, use any valid value of the expected type.
  • NativeFieldMethod.SET : updates the current field value with the specified value. The returned value must be ignored.
  • NativeFieldMethod.GET_SET : reads the current field value before update the field with the specified value. Returns the current field value before update.

Parameters:
obj - the native capable object containing the field.
opcode - the operation code over the field.
value - the new value when updating or any valid value.
Returns:
the current value of the field when reading or any value if writing.

  • NativeFieldMethod.GET_SET : reads the current field value before update the field with the specified value. Returns the current field value before update.

Parameters:

get

java.lang.Object get(java.lang.Object obj)
Returns the current native field value.

The specified value will match the native type of the field.

Current implementation calls call(Object,int,Object) using GET as opcode and as value the default value of the native type wrapped as an Object if necessary (if native type is int, value passed is new Integer(0)).

Parameters:
obj - the native capable object containing the field.
Returns:
the current value of the field.
